    <note type="biography">
        <p>CD and Emma Darwin’s son. Botanist. BA, Cambridge (Trinity College), 1870. Qualified as a physician but did not practise. CD’s secretary from 1874. Collaborated with CD on several botanical projects. Lecturer in botany, Cambridge University, 1884; reader, 1888–1904. Published <hi rend="italic">Life and letters of Charles Darwin</hi> and <hi rend="italic">More letters.</hi> President of the British Association for the Advancement of Science, 1908. Knighted, 1913. FRS 1882.</p></note>
